  "issue_number": 1111,
  "issue_title": "[Bug]: open-PR monitor's local isTestPath misses Python/Ruby test files (foo_test.py, bar_test.rb, baz_spec.rb), wrongly classifying PRs as missing_tests",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\n`missingTestsFromFiles` in `src/signals/contributor-open-pr-monitor.ts` decides whether an open PR ships tests using a **module-local** `isTestPath` helper that is a drifted, narrower copy of the canonical `isTestPath` exported from `src/signals/test-evidence.ts`. The local copy only recognizes Go's `*_test.go` convention and the dotted `.test.`/`.spec.` form; it does **not** recognize the bare `*_test.py`, `*_test.rb`, or `*_spec.rb` conventions that the canonical matcher (and the rest of the signal layer, e.g. `slop.ts`) already handle. As a result, a PR that genuinely adds Python/Ruby tests outside a `test/`/`spec/` directory is classified as having no tests, and the contributor is wrongly told to \"Add or update tests\".\n\nThis affects the open-PR work classification and the next-step guidance shown to contributors.\n\n## Area\n\nSignal logic\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nA PR whose changed files include a conventional Python/Ruby test file (`service_test.py`, `models/widget_test.rb`, `widget_spec.rb`) should be recognized as containing tests, so `missingTestsFromFiles` returns `false` and the PR is not classified `missing_tests`.\n\n## Actual behavior\n\nThe local `isTestPath` (src/signals/contributor-open-pr-monitor.ts) only matches:\n\n```ts\n/(^|\\/)(test|tests|spec|__tests__)\\//i\n/\\.(test|spec)\\.(ts|tsx|js|jsx|py|go|rs)$/i\n/(^|\\/)[^/]+_test\\.go$/i\n```\n\nThe canonical `isTestPath` (src/signals/test-evidence.ts) additionally matches `*_test.py`, `*_test.rb`, `*_spec.rb`, and `src/test/`:\n\n```ts\n/(^|\\/)[^/]+_test\\.(go|py|rb)$/i\n/(^|\\/)[^/]+_spec\\.rb$/i\n/(^|\\/)src\\/test\\//i\n```\n\nFor a PR with changed files `service.py` + `service_test.py`:\n- `codeFiles = [service.py, service_test.py]` (both fail the local matcher), `testFiles = []`\n- `missingTestsFromFiles` returns `codeFiles.length > 0 && testFiles.length === 0` = **true** (wrong)\n- Downstream, `mapPendingClassToWorkClassification` turns this into `\"missing_tests\"` and `buildNextStepPacket` emits \"Add or update tests\" guidance.\n\nThe same happens for `models/widget_test.rb` and `widget_spec.rb`.\n\n## Reproduction\n\nUnit-level: call the internal `missingTestsFromFiles` (exposed via `__contributorOpenPrMonitorInternals`) with `[{ path: \"service.py\" }, { path: \"service_test.py\" }]`. It returns `true` today; it should return `false`.\n\n## Validation\n\nThe divergence is between two helpers in the same `src/signals` package. The canonical `isTestPath` is already reused by `src/signals/slop.ts`, so the maintainer-intended behavior is unambiguous; the local copy is accidental drift. Fix is to delete the local copy and import the canonical one. A regression test belongs in the existing `test/unit/contributor-open-pr-monitor.test.ts`.\n\n## Public-safety check\n\n- [x] I removed secrets, tokens, wallet details, private keys, local paths, and private scoring output.",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-24T20:10:16.000Z",
  "test_cmd": [
    "npm",
    "test",
    "--",
    "--passWithNoTests"
  ],
